  "local_port": 45764,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "Dropping off a U-Haul truck or trailer at a different location is a common practice known as a \"one-way rental.\" Here are the general steps to follow:\n\n1. **Reservation and Confirmation:**\n   - When you initially rent your U-Haul, specify that you want a one-way rental. This means you will pick up the equipment at one location and drop it off at another.\n   - Confirm the drop-off location and ensure it is noted in your rental agreement. This is crucial as not all U-Haul locations may accept one-way rentals for all types of equipment.\n\n2. **Planning Your Drop-Off:**\n   - Plan your route to drop off the U-Haul at the designated location specified in your rental agreement.\n   - Check the operating hours of the drop-off location to ensure you can return the equipment within their business hours.\n\n3. **Return Process:**\n   - Upon arrival, follow any signage or instructions for returning one-way rentals. This may include specific lanes or drop-off areas designated for returns.\n   - If the location has a manned office, you might need to check in with a staff member. If it is after hours, most U-Haul locations have a drop box for keys and return documents.\n\n4. **Inspect Equipment:**\n   - Before completing the drop-off, remove all your belongings from the truck or trailer.\n   - Clean out the vehicle, removing any trash or debris.\n\n5. **Documentation:**\n   - Complete any necessary paperwork. This often includes noting the mileage and fuel level.\n   - Take photos of the fuel gauge and odometer, as well as the exterior condition of the vehicle, for your records.\n\n6. **Key and Contract Return:**\n   - If dropping off during business hours, hand over the keys and finalize your paperwork with a staff member.\n   - For after-hours returns, securely deposit the keys and completed contract in the designated drop box.\n\n7. **Confirmation:**\n   - After returning the equipment, keep an eye out for a confirmation from U-Haul via email or phone confirming the return was processed. If you don't receive confirmation within a reasonable time, contact the drop-off location to ensure everything is in order.\n\nRemember to adhere to the mileage and time limits specified in your rental agreement to avoid additional fees. If you need to make changes to your drop-off plans, contact U-Haul customer service as soon as possible to adjust your reservation.",
